The late 80's/early 90's seemed to be THE prime era for sex comedies like this. Virgin Hunters, while being far from the best, still managed enough laughs and creativity to salvage it from being one of the worst. Our two heroes, Naldo and Vin, along with a female classmate (Sara Brown), travel back in time to stop Camella Swales (Morgan Fairchild) from creating a sexless future.  Tamara Tohill plays the centerfold model Samantha Cummings (yes, her last name is 'Cummings'...wink, wink). Tamara has only done a few films. Sara Suzanne Brown is the shapely young lass on the cover, but sadly only has one nude scene, although later on, we get to see her seriously rocking a red-hot evening dress. Morgan Fairchild plays the headmistress of an all-girls school. Having being jilted some years ago, she's now cynical, uptight and virtually frigid. It took someone like Morgan to pull off that role, but it didn't involve any nudity. For a better look at Ms. Fairchild and all her charms, check out the movie 'The Seduction'. For me, some of the best laughs came from Don Dowe. Now a veteran character actor, this was one of his earliest roles, and as the cyborg Lex 500, he was totally over the top, doing his best Terminator impersonation.

Picture and sound quality for this DVD was very good, and there were some nice extras, including a behind-the-scenes look at the making of the film and interviews with the cast, which sadly, didn't include Fairchild or Don Dowe.
